{
  "stem": "20142.6",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And now we're coming back to this incident of Gesia Street and Zamenhof Street, when the youngsters explode this tank and that tank and immobilize-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] There was not another thing following it.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I remember that we were waiting and seeing, trying to see what actually will happen to it.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And then we-- they came during the night.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was pitch dark and there were no lights involved.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That-- they pulled the tank out-- out of the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And what they had done with it, I don't know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But it must have been of some value to them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] There was a [INAUDIBLE] feeling to see the turret of the tank open and the gun hanging with the nose down.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I didn't see how they pulled it out, but I believe they did, because the following day I didn't see any of the thing-- of the parts of tank in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "However, what we are very much concerned is that little kid that was-- jumped on the tank.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "We couldn't find the body of the child either.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "If there is any positive things of the thing, how did we survive, well, on the way to the bunker of-- of Antek Zuckerman, I had to enter the bunker on [INAUDIBLE] 4, because the shots of the German approaching were too close.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And yeah-- I asked for help to enter the bunker.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "About-- that was on May the 5th that the Germans somehow got to our bunker and I was in there.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And they threw in tear gas.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And we start choking and we're gasping for air.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And finally, they said to us, we will not shoot at you.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Just raise your hands above your head and come out with the weapons up.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
